                                Matters in the Independent Auditor’s Report</i> (AU-C sec.
                            701) <unknown id="UUID-9a1b63a3-6faf-2f41-2eaf-f88a20adbbe6_N661755007b549" class="- topic/unknown ">AU-C Section 701</unknown>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ul>
         <p outputclass="box" class="- topic/p ">
            <xref format="dita" class="- topic/xref " href="../../../ps/ad_us_auditing_standards_aicpa_clarified/ad_section_500_599/ad_540/ad_540.dita#UUID-5e295753-fd8e-ad8d-74c0-3d4d49ef0274">SAS No. 143</xref> addresses the auditor’s responsibilities relating to
                    accounting estimates, including fair value accounting estimates and related
                    disclosures, in an audit of financial statements. This SAS is effective for
                    audits of financial statements for periods ending on or after December 15, 2023.
                    A link to the final SAS and other resources can be found on the page “<xref scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref " href="https://www.aicpa.org/interestareas/frc/auditattest/auditing-standards-information-and-resources.html">Recently Issued Auditing and Attestation Standards: Information and
                        Resources</xref>,” which is available using the audit and attest link in the
                    financial reporting center at aicpa.org. <unknown id="UUID-9a1b63a3-6faf-2f41-2eaf-f88a20adbbe6_N661755007ca2e" class="- topic/unknown ">AU-C Section 540</unknown>
         </p>
      </note>
